@{u}RealTime@{uu}:-

RealTime is only a small program, so it would be pointless classing it as
Shareware and demanding huge sums of money from people :) So I decided to
make it PostcardWare, so if you use this program, and it comes in very handy
then @{"send" link "Author" 0} me a postcard letting me know.

This program was fairly bug ridden from version 1.0, but through plenty of
testing now appears to be bug free.  It made from 1.0 through to 1.2 just
with bug fixes, and thanks to Gordon Brown, Phil Brown and me for testing
it.

@{u}Future@{uu}:-

I don't think there's much call for future versions, what else can I add?
One thing I do intend to impelment in 1.3 is a standard date form. At the
moment it stores the date in a non-ASCII format, version 1.3 will output the
date as an ASCII file similar to the output from C:Date.  Also a Save As
option to specify the output file, and an update option, to simply update
the current time/date to the file without the GUI.  These three will be
fitted into 1.3, and hopefully we won't need a 1.4 bug fix :)@{fg filltext}

